  Locus:
    Date: 20 August 2017
    Chapter: 47
  Copyright: 2002
  Translator: Douglas Allchin
---
Never venturing abroad,
one may know the world entire.
Never casting forth one's gaze,
one may see the Way of heaven.

The farther one goes,
the less one knows.

Know, without stirring.
See, without looking.
Work, without doing.
